-10%2F8pvsg1ko_greater-noida-car-fire_625x300_23_October_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fnoida-news%2Ftoyota-fortuner-catches-fire-burnt-body-found-cops-probe-murder-angle-6853319%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Locals%20first%20spotted%20the%20burning%20car%2C%20following%20which%20they%20tried%20to%20pull%20the%20victim%20out.%20However%2C%20they%20were%20unsuccessful%2C%20the%20police%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fnoida-news%2Ftoyota-fortuner-catches-fire-burnt-body-found-cops-probe-murder-angle-6853319%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BWasn't%20Aware%20Permission%20Needed%26quot%3B%3A%20Delhi%20Lt%20Governor%20On%20Tree%20Felling%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EDelhi%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20VK%20Saxena%20has%20told%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20he%20was%20not%20aware%20that%20the%20court's%20permission%20was%20needed%20for%20the%20felling%20of%20600%20trees%20in%20the%20capital's%20Ridge%20area%2C%20which%20is%20an%20extension%20of%20the%20Aravallis.%20His%20submission%20came%20in%20a%20personal%20affidavit%20ahead%20of%20Wednesday's%20hearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20had%20asked%20Mr%20Saxena%2C%20who%20is%20also%20the%20chairperson%20of%20the%20Delhi%20Development%20Authority%20(DDA)%2C%20to%20submit%20a%20personal%20affidavit%20with%20the%20details%20of%20his%20visit%20to%20the%20area%20on%20February%203%20and%20explaining%20what%20steps%20were%20being%20taken%20to%20fix%20responsibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20was%20also%20told%20to%20specify%20if%20there%20was%20any%20discussion%20about%20permission%20for%20cutting%20trees%20and%20when%20he%20came%20to%20know%20about%20the%20requirement%20of%20court%20permission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERead%20%7C%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fvk-saxena-delhi-ridge-area-file-personal-affidavit-in-ridge-tree-cutting-case-supreme-court-to-delhi-lieutenant-governor-6802941%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BFile%20Personal%20Affidavit%20In%20Ridge%20Tree-Cutting%20Case%26quot%3B%3A%20Supreme%20Court%20To%20Delhi%20Lt%20Governor%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Saxena%20said%20in%20his%20affidavit%20he%20had%20visited%20the%20Ridge%20area%20where%20a%20medical%20facility%20is%20set%20to%20come%20up%20for%20the%20CAPF%2C%20on%20February%203.%20During%20this%20visit%2C%20he%20took%20into%20account%20the%20importance%20and%20necessity%20of%20the%20project%20as%20well%20as%20the%20resources%20already%20invested%20in%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20returning%2C%20he%20stopped%20at%20the%20site%20of%20road%20widening%2C%20but%20no%20one%20present%20at%20the%20site%20brought%20to%20his%20notice%20that%20the%20court's%20permission%20was%20needed%20to%20fell%20trees%20there%2C%20the%20affidavit%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20said%20he%20was%20made%20aware%20about%20it%20only%20on%20March%2021%20after%20an%20application%20was%20filed%20by%20DDA%20seeking%20permission%20for%20the%20felling%20of%20trees%20for%20the%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20regards%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20actual%20act%20of%20felling%20of%20trees%20had%20commenced%20on%20or%20about%2016.02.2024%20was%20brought%20to%20the%20notice%20of%20the%20undersigned%20vide%20letter%20of%20Vice%20Chairman%2C%20DDA%20dated%2010.06.2024%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20affidavit%20identified%20the%20officers%20responsible%20for%20the%20tree%20felling%20as%20Manoj%20Kumar%20Yadav%2C%20the%20DDA%20executive%20engineer%20who%20had%20given%20the%20instructions%20to%20cut%20the%20trees%20to%20the%20contractor%2C%20and%20Pawan%20Kumar%20and%20Ayush%20Saraswat%2C%20both%20from%20the%20engineering%20division%20of%20the%20DDA%2C%20who%20were%20responsible%20for%20permitting%20the%20act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20named%20Pankaj%20Verma%2C%20Superintending%20Engineer%2C%20and%20Mr%20Yadav%20as%20the%20officials%20responsible%20for%20suppressing%20facts%20from%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20hearing%20a%20contempt%20case%20against%20some%20DDA%20and%20Delhi%20government%20officials%20over%20the%20axing%20of%20trees.%20It%20had%20said%20that%20if%20the%20chairperson%20agrees%2C%20criminal%20action%20must%20be%20taken%20against%20the%20officers%20responsible%20for%20the%20tree%20cutting.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729667520000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2F5hdcar4g_ridge-tree-cutting_625x300_16_May_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwasnt-aware-permission-needed-delhi-lt-governor-to-supreme-court-on-tree-felling-6853236%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Delhi%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20VK%20Saxena%20has%20told%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20he%20was%20not%20aware%20that%20the%20court's%20permission%20was%20needed%20for%20the%20felling%20of%20600%20trees%20in%20the%20capital's%20Ridge%20area%2C%20which%20is%20an%20extension%20of%20the%20Aravallis.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwasnt-aware-permission-needed-delhi-lt-governor-to-supreme-court-on-tree-felling-6853236%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20LAC%20Pact%3A%20Will%20China's%20Words%20Match%20Its%20Actions%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2Ffe70pjro_china_625x300_23_October_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20and%20China%20have%20decided%20to%20bury%20the%20hatchet%2C%20almost%20and%20for%20now.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20there%20will%20be%20a%20bilateral%20meeting%20between%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20today%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20BRICS%20Summit%20in%20Kazan%2C%20Russia.%20In%20a%20major%20breakthrough%20that%20can%20potentially%20end%20the%20over%20four-year-long%20military%20standoff%2C%20the%20two%20neighbours%20have%20reached%20an%20agreement%20on%20patrolling%20along%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%20(LAC)%20in%20eastern%20Ladakh%20%26quot%3Bleading%20to%20disengagement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20militaries%20of%20the%20two%20nations%20had%20already%20pulled%20back%20from%20four%20of%20six%20friction%20points%20in%20eastern%20Ladakh%2C%20including%20the%20Galwan%20Valley%2C%20the%20site%20of%20a%20violent%20clash%20in%20June%202020%2C%20the%20latest%20pact%20pertains%20to%20patrolling%20in%20Depsang%20and%20Demchok%20areas.%20With%20this%2C%20External%20Affairs%20Minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%20confirmed%20that%20the%20agreement%20on%20border%20patrols%20signalled%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20disengagement%20process%20with%20China%20has%20been%20completed%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Long-Drawn%20Conflict%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20formidable%20military%20forces%20have%20been%20locked%20in%20an%20eyeball-to-eyeball%20confrontation%20since%20May%202020%2C%20with%20New%20Delhi%20making%20it%20clear%20that%20there%20cannot%20be%20any%20normalcy%20in%20the%20bilateral%20relationship%20till%20the%20situation%20is%20not%20restored%20to%20pre-2020%20status%20at%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%20(LAC).%20The%20Galwan%20incident%20of%20June%2015%2C%202020%2C%20which%20was%20the%20most%20serious%20military%20conflict%20between%20the%20two%20sides%20in%20decades%20and%20the%20deadliest%20since%20the%201962%20war%2C%20resulted%20in%20India%20losing%2020%20soldiers%20and%20the%20PLA%20losing%20as%20many%20as%2040%20personnel%2C%20even%20though%20China%20has%20acknowledged%20only%20four%20casualties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20has%20been%20a%20major%20inflexion%20point%20in%20Indian%20policy%20towards%20China%20as%20well%20as%20the%20wider%20geopolitical%20churn%20shaping%20the%20Indo-Pacific.%20New%20Delhi%20dramatically%20recalibrated%20its%20ties%20with%20Beijing%20across%20a%20full%20range%20of%20sectors%20and%20mobilised%20at%20a%20national%20level%20to%20take%20the%20China%20challenge%20head-on.%20From%20foreign%20policy%20to%20economy%2C%20from%20infrastructure%20to%20people-to-people%20engagement%2C%20a%20re-appraisal%20was%20undertaken%20and%20a%20recalibration%20was%20the%20result.%20China's%20belligerence%20was%20met%20with%20an%20unprecedented%20Indian%20resoluteness%20as%20a%20whole-of-government%20approach%20exemplified%20a%20newfound%20willingness%20in%20New%20Delhi%20to%20not%20shy%20away%20from%20taking%20difficult%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%20Is%20More%20Prepared%20Now%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20it%20is%20this%20resolve%20by%20New%20Delhi%20that%20seems%20to%20have%20paid%20off%20with%20the%20agreement%20on%20disengagement.%20There%20are%20lots%20of%20issues%20that%20remain%20shrouded%20in%20secrecy%20and%20will%20only%20reveal%20themselves%20once%20the%20details%20of%20the%20new%20pact%20are%20out.%20As%20India%20looks%20for%20a%20return%20to%20status%20quo%20ante%2C%20the%20massive%20infrastructure%20that%20China%20has%20created%20along%20the%20border%20with%20India%20is%20unlikely%20to%20disappear%20any%20time%20soon.%20What%20has%20happened%2C%20as%20a%20result%2C%20however%2C%20is%20that%20India%20has%20managed%20to%20get%20its%20act%20together%20on%20the%20infrastructure%20front%20as%20well.%20So%2C%20unlike%20the%20pre-May%202020%20period%2C%20Indian%20logistical%20presence%20along%20the%20border%20is%20much%20stronger%2C%20and%2C%20hopefully%2C%20there%20won't%20be%20any%20let%20up%20in%20its%20building%20up%20of%20its%20own%20infrastructure%20on%20its%20side%20of%20the%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20issue%20is%20related%20to%20how%20China%20is%20perceived%20in%20India%20now.%20Whatever%20the%20diplomatese%2C%20the%20reality%20remains%20that%20trust%20in%20Beijing%2C%20which%20was%20already%20low%2C%20seems%20to%20have%20completely%20disappeared%20not%20only%20in%20the%20Indian%20political%20establishment%20but%20also%20in%20the%20society%20at%20large.%20It%20is%20for%20China%20now%20to%20rebuild%20that%20trust%2C%20not%20through%20its%20words%20but%20by%20its%20actions.%20Repeated%20violations%20of%20agreements%20have%20now%20led%20to%20a%20new%20reality%20where%20any%20new%20pact%20with%20China%20will%20struggle%20to%20regain%20legitimacy%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20ordinary%20Indians%2C%20making%20the%20job%20of%20Indian%20diplomats%20even%20harder.%20After%20all%2C%20there%20was%20an%20attempt%20to%20create%20a%20'Wuhan%20spirit'%20after%20the%20Doklam%20debacle%2C%20only%20to%20lead%20to%20Galwan!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20China%20Accept%20India%20As%20A%20Peer%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20while%20the%20latest%20agreement%20can%20be%20the%20starting%20point%20for%20rebuilding%20confidence%20between%20the%20two%20neighbours%2C%20the%20border%20problem%20is%20a%20manifestation%20of%20a%20wider%20issue%20facing%20Sino-Indian%20relations.%20The%20two%20rising%20powers%20are%20now%20structural%20rivals%2C%20and%20the%20inability%20of%20China%20to%20accept%20India%20as%20a%20peer%20or%20to%20be%20sensitive%20to%20New%20Delhi's%20core%20security%20concerns%20has%20been%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20deteriorating%20ties%20between%20the%20two%20Asian%20giants.%20This%20latest%20agreement%20does%20nothing%20to%20alter%20that%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Indians%20at%20large%2C%20the%20question%20still%20remains%20whether%20China%20indeed%20wants%20to%20move%20towards%20a%20lasting%20solution%20to%20the%20boundary%20dispute%2C%20or%20whether%20this%20is%20another%20tactical%20attempt%20at%20buying%20time%20as%20both%20China%20and%20India%20continue%20their%20ascent%20in%20the%20global%20interstate%20hierarchy.%20Nonetheless%2C%20what%20is%20clear%20is%20that%20New%20Delhi's%20resolve%20in%20frontally%20challenging%20China's%20expansionism%20has%20paid%20off.%20Even%20as%20India%20would%20be%20engaging%20with%20China%20after%20the%20latest%20agreement%2C%20it%20would%20be%20worth%20remembering%20that%20there%20is%20no%20substitute%20for%20building%20inherent%20capacity%20and%20leveraging%20external%20partnerships%20to%20effectively%20manage%20a%20potentially%20malevolent%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Harsh%20V.%20Pant%20is%20Vice%20President%20%E2%80%93%20Studies%20and%20Foreign%20Policy%2C%20at%20Observer%20Research%20Foundation%2C%20and%20Professor%20of%20International%20Relations%20at%20King's%20College%20London.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729667340000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2Fdh5bnqko_china_625x300_23_October_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findia-china-lac-pact-will-beijings-words-match-its-actions-6853622%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22For%20Indians%20at%20large%2C%20the%20question%20still%20remains%20whether%20China%20indeed%20wants%20to%20move%20towards%20a%20lasting%20solution%20to%20the%20boundary%20dispute%2C%20or%20whether%20this%20is%20another%20tactical%20attempt%20at%20buying%20time%20as%20both%20China%20and%20India%20continue%20their%20ascent.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SC%20reverses%20NCLAT%20order%20approving%20Byju's%20Rs%20158%20cr%20dues%20settlement%20with%20BCCI%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3