S%20states%20of%20Colorado%20and%20Nebraska.%20The%20slivered%20onions%20used%20in%20the%20burgers%20are%20suspected%20to%20be%20the%20source%20of%20contamination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20E.%20coli%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEscherichia%20coli%20(E.%20coli)%20is%20a%20type%20of%20bacteria%20commonly%20found%20in%20the%20intestines%20of%20humans%20and%20animals.%20While%20most%20strains%20of%20E.%20coli%20are%20harmless%20and%20help%20maintain%20gut%20health%2C%20some%20can%20cause%20serious%20foodborne%20illness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EE.%20coli%20outbreak%20at%20McDonald's%3A%20What's%20happening%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fecoli%2Foutbreaks%2Fwhere-people-got-sick-e-coli-o157-2024.html%C2%A0%5C%22%3ECDC%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20along%20with%20the%20Food%20and%20Drug%20Administration%20(FDA)%2C%20identified%20onions%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Blikely%20source%2C%26quot%3B%20leading%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fmcdonalds-responds-to-e-coli-bacterial-outbreak-linked-to-its-quarter-pounder-hamburgers-in-us-6852564%5C%22%3EMcDonald's%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20suspend%20sales%20of%20Quarter%20Pounders%20in%2012%20states%2C%20including%20Colorado%2C%20Nebraska%2C%20Kansas%20and%20Utah.%20The%20fast-food%20chain%20has%20also%20stopped%20using%20the%20onions%20in%20question%2C%20although%20investigations%20are%20underway%20to%20determine%20whether%20the%20hamburger%20patties%20themselves%20could%20also%20be%20contributing%20to%20the%20outbreak.%20The%20outbreak%20was%20tied%20to%20E.%20coli%20O157.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%2010%20people%2C%20including%20a%20child%20with%20a%20complicating%20illness%2C%20have%20been%20hospitalised%2C%20while%20a%20Colorado%20resident%20has%20died.%20The%20CDC's%20investigation%20suggests%20the%20actual%20number%20of%20sick%20people%20may%20be%20higher%20than%20reported%2C%20as%2