0an%20E.%20coli%20outbreak%20linked%20to%20the%20fast%20food%20chain's%20Quarter%20Pounders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20health%20agency%20said%20the%20%26quot%3Bfast-moving%26quot%3B%20outbreak%20is%20primarily%20affecting%20people%20in%20Nebraska%20and%20Colorado.%20It%20added%20that%20most%20people%20affected%20reported%20eating%20a%20Quarter%20Pounder%20hamburger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20internal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcorporate.mcdonalds.com%2Fcorpmcd%2Four-stories%2Farticle%2Falways-putting-food-safety-first.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emessage%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20to%20the%20company's%20website%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20Cesar%20Pi%C3%B1a%2C%20McDonald's%20North%20America%20chief%20supply%20chain%20officer%2C%20said%20the%20chain%20is%20taking%20%26quot%3Bswift%20and%20decisive%26quot%3B%20action%20in%20response%20to%20the%20outbreak.%20The%20statement%20said%20the%20illnesses%20may%20be%20linked%20to%20slivered%20onions%20used%20in%20the%20Quarter%20Pounders%2C%20which%20are%20sourced%20by%20a%20single%20supplier%20that%20serves%20three%20distribution%20centers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcDonald's%20is%20temporarily%20removing%20the%20burgers%20from%20restaurants%20in%20Colorado%2C%20Kansas%2C%20Utah%2C%20Wyoming%2C%20and%20parts%20of%20Idaho%2C%20Iowa%2C%20Missouri%2C%20Montana%2C%20Nebraska%2C%20Nevada%2C%20New%20Mexico%2C%20and%20Oklahoma%2C%20the%20statement%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20take%20food%20safety%20extremely%20seriously%20and%20it's%20the%20right%20thing%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Pi%C3%B1a%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20total%20of%2049%20cases%20across%2010%20states%20have%20been%20reported%20so%20far%2C%20but%20the%20extent%20of%20the%20outbreak%20is%20%26quot%3Blikely%20much%20higher%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20CDC%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CDC%20said%20McDonald's%20has%20removed%20some%20ingredients%20from%20its%20burgers%20and%20paused%20sales%20of%20Quarter%20Pounders%20in%20some%20states.%20Investigators%20are%20working%20t